#A simple Ruby script that fetches a random joke from the Official Joke API and displays it in the terminal.

#Requirements
#Ruby 2.x or higher

#Setup

#Install Ruby: If you haven't installed Ruby, you can download it from the official website: https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/documentation/installation/

#Download the script: You can create a new file and paste the following code into it:

#ruby
#Copy code

#Run the script using the command:

#The script will fetch a random joke and display it in the terminal.

#Example Output:
#Why don't skeletons fight each other? - They don't have the guts.
